# Guinea Pigs of Neverwinter
# One D&D Cleric Class Features
# load_yaml(get_gvar("c958b431-f455-463b-bfb3-38138ea122b0"))

"Cleric: Divine Order":
  title: "Cleric Level 1: Divine Order"
  desc: "You have dedicated yourself to one of the following sacred roles of your choice:\n\n**Protector**. Trained for battle, you gain Martial Weapon proficiency and Heavy Armor training.\n\n**Thaumaturge**. You know one extra cantrip from the Divine spell list (see your Spellcasting feature for information on preparing spells). In addition, your mystical connection to the divine gives you a bonus to your Intelligence (Religion) checks. The bonus equals your Wisdom modifier (minimum of +1)."
  fields:
  - body: "[Packet 6](https://www.dndbeyond.com/sources/ua/ph-playtest-6)"

"Cleric: Spellcasting":
  title: "Cleric Level 1: Spellcasting"
  desc: "You have learned to cast spells through prayer, meditation, and devotion. [See the _Player's Handbook_ for the rules on spellcasting](https://www.dndbeyond.com/sources/phb/spellcasting). The information below details how you use those rules as a Cleric."
  fields:
  - title: Cantrips
    body: "You know three cantrips of your choice from the Divine spell list. Rather than choosing, you may start with _Guidance_, _Sacred Flame_, and _Thaumaturgy_.\n\nWhenever you gain a Cleric level, you can replace one of your cantrips with another cantrip of your choice from the Divine spell list.\n\nWhen you reach 4th and 10th level in this class, you learn another cantrip of your choice from the Divine spell list, as shown in the Cantrips column of the Cleric table."
  - title: Spell Slots
    body: "The Cleric table shows how many spell slots you have to cast your spells of 1st level and higher. To cast one of these spells, you must expend a slot of the spell's level or higher. You regain all expended spell slots when you finish a Long Rest."
  - title: Prepared Spells of 1st+ Level
    body: "You prepare the list of spells of 1st level and higher that are available for you to cast with this feature. To start, choose four 1st-level spells from the Divine spell list. Rather than choosing, you may start with _Bless_, _Cure Wounds_, _Guiding Bolt_, and _Shield of Faith_.\n\nThe number of spells on your list also increases as you gain Cleric levels, as shown in the Prepared Spells column of the Cleric table. Whenever that number increases, choose additional spells from the Divine spell list until the number of spells on your list matches the number on the table. The chosen spells must be of a level for which you have spell slots. For example, if you're a 3rd-level Cleric, your list of prepared spells can include six spells of 1st or 2nd level, in any combination.\n\nIf another Cleric feature gives spells that you always have prepared, those spells don't count against the number of spells on the list you prepare with this Spellcasting feature, but those spells otherwise follow the rules in this feature."
  - title: Changing Your Prepared Spells
    body: "Whenever you finish a Long Rest, you can change your list of prepared spells, replacing one or more of the spells there with other Divine spells for which you have spell slots. Preparing a new list requires time spent in prayer and meditation: at least 1 minute per spell level for each spell you add to the list."
  - title: Spellcasting Ability
    body: "Wisdom is your Spellcasting Ability for your Cleric spells."
  - title: Spellcasting Focus
    body: "You can use a Holy Symbol as a Spellcasting Focus for the spells you prepare for this class."
  - title: "Cleric Table: Cantrips and Prepared Spells"
    body: "```\n| Level | Cantrips | Prepared Spells\n|-------+----------+-----------------\n|   1st |     3    |        4\n|   2nd |     3    |        5\n|   3rd |     3    |        6\n|   4th |     4    |        7\n|   5th |     4    |        9\n|   6th |     4    |       10\n|   7th |     4    |       11\n|   8th |     4    |       12\n|   9th |     4    |       14\n|  10th |     5    |       15\n|  11th |     5    |       16\n|  12th |     5    |       16\n|  13th |     5    |       17\n|  14th |     5    |       17\n|  15th |     5    |       18\n|  16th |     5    |       18\n|  17th |     5    |       19\n|  18th |     5    |       20\n|  19th |     5    |       21\n|  20th |     5    |       22\n```"
  - title: "Cleric Table: Spell Slots"
    body: "```\n| Level | 1st 2nd 3rd 4th 5th 6th 7th 8th 9th\n|-------+-------------------------------------\n|   1st |  2   —   —   —   —   —   —   —   —\n|   2nd |  3   —   —   —   —   —   —   —   —\n|   3rd |  4   2   —   —   —   —   —   —   —\n|   4th |  4   3   —   —   —   —   —   —   —\n|   5th |  4   3   2   —   —   —   —   —   —\n|   6th |  4   3   3   —   —   —   —   —   —\n|   7th |  4   3   3   1   —   —   —   —   —\n|   8th |  4   3   3   2   —   —   —   —   —\n|   9th |  4   3   3   3   1   —   —   —   —\n|  10th |  4   3   3   3   2   —   —   —   —\n|  11th |  4   3   3   3   2   1   —   —   —\n|  12th |  4   3   3   3   2   1   —   —   —\n|  13th |  4   3   3   3   2   1   1   —   —\n|  14th |  4   3   3   3   2   1   1   —   —\n|  15th |  4   3   3   3   2   1   1   1   —\n|  16th |  4   3   3   3   2   1   1   1   —\n|  17th |  4   3   3   3   2   1   1   1   1\n|  18th |  4   3   3   3   2   1   1   1   1\n|  19th |  4   3   3   3   2   2   1   1   1\n|  20th |  4   3   3   3   2   2   2   1   1\n```"
  - body: "[Packet 6](https://www.dndbeyond.com/sources/ua/ph-playtest-6)"

"Cleric: Channel Divinity":
  title: "Cleric Level 2: Channel Divinity"
  desc: "You gain the ability to channel divine energy directly from the Outer Planes, using that energy to fuel magical effects. You start with two such effects: Divine Spark and Turn Undead, each of which is described below. Each time you use your Channel Divinity, you choose which effect to create, and you gain additional effect options at higher levels in this class.\n\nYou can use Channel Divinity twice. You regain one expended use when you finish a Short Rest, and you regain all expended uses when you finish a Long Rest. You gain additional uses when you reach certain Cleric levels, as shown in the Channel Divinity column of the Cleric table.\n\nIf a Channel Divinity effect requires a saving throw, the DC equals the Spell Save DC from this class's Spellcasting feature."
  fields:
  - title: "Divine Spark"
    body: "As a Magic action, you point your Holy Symbol at another creature you can see within 30 feet of yourself and focus divine energy at them. Roll 1d8 and add your Wisdom modifier. You either restore Hit Points to the creature equal to that total or force the creature to make a Constitution saving throw. On a failed save, the creature takes Necrotic or Radiant (your choice) damage equal to that total. On a successful save, the creature takes half as much damage (round down).\n\nYou roll an additional d8 when you reach certain Cleric levels: 7th level (2d8), 13th level (3d8), and 18th level (4d8)."
  - title: "Turn Undead"
    body: "As a Magic action, you present your Holy Symbol and speak a prayer censuring Undead creatures. Each Undead within 30 feet of you must make a Wisdom saving throw. If the creature fails its saving throw, it has the Frightened and Incapacitated conditions for 1 minute. This effect ends early on the creature if it takes any damage, you have the Incapacitated condition, or you die."
  - title: "Cleric Table: Channel Divinity Uses"
    body: "```\n| Level | Channel Divinity\n|-------+------------------\n|   1st | —\n|   2nd | 2\n|   3rd | 2\n|   4th | 2\n|   5th | 2\n|   6th | 3\n|   7th | 3\n|   8th | 3\n|   9th | 3\n|  10th | 3\n|  11th | 3\n|  12th | 3\n|  13th | 3\n|  14th | 3\n|  15th | 3\n|  16th | 3\n|  17th | 3\n|  18th | 4\n|  19th | 4\n|  20th | 4\n```"
  - body: "[Packet 6](https://www.dndbeyond.com/sources/ua/ph-playtest-6)"

"Cleric: Cleric Subclass":
  title: "Cleric Level 3: Cleric Subclass"
  desc: "You gain a Cleric subclass of your choice: Life Domain, Light Domain, Trickery Domain, or War Domain. Subclasses are detailed after this class's description.\n\nA subclass is a specialization that grants you special abilities at certain Cleric levels. For the rest of your career, you gain each of your subclass's features that are of your Cleric level and lower."
  fields:
  - title: "At 6th and Level 17"
    body: "You gain a feature from your Cleric subclass."
  - body: "[Packet 6](https://www.dndbeyond.com/sources/ua/ph-playtest-6)"

"Cleric: Ability Score Improvement":
  title: "Cleric Level 4: Ability Score Improvement"
  desc: "You gain the Ability Score Improvement feat or another feat of your choice for which you qualify."
  fields:
  - title: "At 8th, 12th, 16th, and Level 19"
    body: "You gain the Ability Score Improvement feat or another feat of your choice for which you qualify."
  - body: "[Packet 6](https://www.dndbeyond.com/sources/ua/ph-playtest-6)"

"Cleric: Smite Undead":
  title: "Cleric Level 5: Smite Undead"
  desc: "You can cause your Turn Undead feature to smite the undying; whenever you use Turn Undead, you can roll a number of d8s equal to your Wisdom modifier (minimum of 1d8) and add the rolls together. Each Undead that fails its saving throw against that use of Turn Undead takes Radiant damage equal to the roll's total. This damage doesn't end the turn effect."
  fields:
  - body: "[Packet 6](https://www.dndbeyond.com/sources/ua/ph-playtest-6)"

"Cleric: Blessed Strikes":
  title: "Cleric Level 7: Blessed Strikes"
  desc: "Divine power infuses you in battle. You gain one of the following options of your choice:\n\n**_Divine Strike_**. Once on each of your turns when you hit a creature with an attack with a weapon, you can cause the target to take an extra 1d8 Necrotic or Radiant (your choice) damage.\n\n**_Potent Spellcasting_**. You add your Wisdom modifier to the damage you deal with any Divine cantrip.\n\nIf you get either option from another source, you use only the option you chose for this feature."
  fields:
  - body: "[Packet 6](https://www.dndbeyond.com/sources/ua/ph-playtest-6)"

"Cleric: Commune":
  title: "Cleric Level 9: Commune"
  desc: "In the past, you have reached the divine source of your power through prayer. Now, you can also have brief conversations; you always have the _Commune_ spell prepared."
  fields:
  - body: "[Packet 6](https://www.dndbeyond.com/sources/ua/ph-playtest-6)"

"Cleric: Divine Intervention":
  title: "Cleric Level 10: Divine Intervention"
  desc: "You can call on your deity or pantheon to intervene on your behalf. As a Magic action, choose any Divine spell of level 5 or lower that doesn't require a Reaction to cast. As part of the same action, you cast that spell without expending a spell slot or needing material components. You then can't use this feature again until you finish a Long Rest."
  fields:
  - body: "[Packet 6](https://www.dndbeyond.com/sources/ua/ph-playtest-6)"

"Cleric: Improved Blessed Strikes":
  title: "Cleric Level 14: Blessed Strikes"
  desc: "The option you chose for Blessed Strikes grows more powerful:\n\n**Divine Strike**. The extra damage of your Divine Strike increases to 2d8.\n\n**Potent Spellcasting**. When you cast a Divine cantrip and deal damage to a creature with it, you can give vitality to yourself or another creature within 60 feet of yourself, granting a number of Temporary Hit Points equal to twice your Wisdom modifier."
  fields:
  - body: "[Packet 6](https://www.dndbeyond.com/sources/ua/ph-playtest-6)"

"Cleric: Greater Divine Intervention":
  title: "Cleric Level 20: Greater Divine Intervention"
  desc: "You are able to call on even more powerful divine intervention. When you use your Divine Intervention feature, you can choose _Wish_ when you select a spell. If you do so, you can't use Divine Intervention again until you finish 2d4 Long Rests.\n\nWhen you cast _Wish_ with this feature, you are immune to the stress caused by using _Wish_ to do something other than casting a spell."
  fields:
  - body: "[Packet 6](https://www.dndbeyond.com/sources/ua/ph-playtest-6)"


# ===================================
# CLERIC: LIFE DOMAIN FEATURES
# ===================================

"Life Domain: Domain Spells":
  title: "Life Domain Level 3: Domain Spells"
  desc: "Your connection to this divine domain ensures you always have certain spells ready. When you reach a Cleric level specified in the Life Domain Spells table, you thereafter always have the listed spells prepared."
  fields:
  - title: "Life Domain Spells"
    body: "```\n| Cleric |\n| Level  | Prepared Spells\n|--------+-----------------\n| 3rd    | Aid, Bless, Cure Wounds, Lesser Restoration\n| 5th    | Mass Healing Word, Revivify\n| 7th    | Aura of Life, Death Ward\n| 9th    | Greater Restoration, Mass Cure Wounds\n```"
  - body: "[Packet 6](https://www.dndbeyond.com/sources/ua/ph-playtest-6)"

"Life Domain: Disciple of Life":
  title: "Life Domain Level 3: Disciple of Life"
  desc: "Your healing spells are empowered by life itself. When a spell you cast with a spell slot restores Hit Points to a creature, that creature regains additional Hit Points on the turn you cast the spell. The additional Hit Points equal 2 plus the spell slot's level."
  fields:
  - body: "[Packet 6](https://www.dndbeyond.com/sources/ua/ph-playtest-6)"

"Life Domain: Preserve Life":
  title: "Life Domain Level 3: Preserve Life"
  desc: "As part of casting a prepared Abjuration spell from the Divine spell list, you can expend uses of Channel Divinity to create a spell slot to use for the casting. You must expend a number of Channel Divinity uses equal to the spell's level. For example, you can expend one use of Channel Divinity to create a 1st-level spell slot for a casting of _Shield of Faith_ if you have that spell prepared."
  fields:
  - body: "[Packet 6](https://www.dndbeyond.com/sources/ua/ph-playtest-6)"

"Life Domain: Blessed Healer":
  title: "Life Domain Level 6: Blessed Healer"
  desc: "The healing spells you cast on others heal you as well. Immediately after you cast a spell with a spell slot that restores Hit Points to one creature other than you, you regain Hit Points equal to 2 plus the spell slot's level."
  fields:
  - body: "[Packet 6](https://www.dndbeyond.com/sources/ua/ph-playtest-6)"

"Life Domain: Supreme Healing":
  title: "Life Domain Level 17: Supreme Healing"
  desc: "When you would normally roll one or more dice to restore Hit Points to a creature with a spell or Channel Divinity, don't roll those dice for the healing; instead, use the highest number possible for each die. For example, instead of restoring 2d6 Hit Points to a creature with a spell, you restore 12."
  fields:
  - body: "[Packet 6](https://www.dndbeyond.com/sources/ua/ph-playtest-6)"


# ===================================
# CLERIC: LIGHT DOMAIN FEATURES
# ===================================

"Light Domain: Domain Spells":
  title: "Light Domain Level 3: Domain Spells"
  desc: "Your connection to this divine domain ensures you always have certain spells ready. When you reach a Cleric level specified in the Light Domain Spells table, you thereafter always have the listed spells prepared."
  fields:
  - title: "Light Domain Spells"
    body: "```\n| Cleric |\n| Level  | Prepared Spells\n|--------+-----------------\n| 3rd    | Burning Hands, Faerie Fire, Moonbeam, See Invisibility\n| 5th    | Daylight, Fireball\n| 7th    | Arcane Eye, Wall of Fire\n| 9th    | Flame Strike, Scrying\n```"
  - body: "[Packet 6](https://www.dndbeyond.com/sources/ua/ph-playtest-6)"

"Light Domain: Warding Flare":
  title: "Light Domain Level 3: Warding Flare"
  desc: "When a creature that you can see within 30 feet of you makes an attack roll, you can use your Reaction to impose Disadvantage on the attack roll, causing light to flare before the attacker before it hits or misses.\n\nYou can use this feature a number of times equal to your Wisdom modifier (minimum of once). You regain all expended uses when you finish a Long Rest."
  fields:
  - body: "[Packet 6](https://www.dndbeyond.com/sources/ua/ph-playtest-6)"

"Light Domain: Radiance of the Dawn":
  title: "Light Domain Level 3: Radiance of the Dawn"
  desc: "As a Magic action, you present your Holy Symbol and expend a use of your Channel Divinity to emit sunlight in a 30-foot-radius sphere centered on yourself. Any magical darkness—such as that created by the Darkness spell—in the sphere is dispelled. Additionally, each creature of your choice in the sphere must make a Constitution saving throw, taking Radiant damage equal to 2d10 + your Cleric level on a failed save, or half as much damage on a successful one."
  fields:
  - body: "[Packet 6](https://www.dndbeyond.com/sources/ua/ph-playtest-6)"

"Light Domain: Revealing Light":
  title: "Light Domain Level 6: Revealing Light"
  desc: "As a Bonus Action, you can present your Holy Symbol and cast See Invisibility without expending a spell slot. When you cast it in this way, your allies also gain the benefit of the spell while within 10 feet of you. Until the spell ends, you emit Bright Light in a 10-foot radius and Dim Light for an additional 10 feet. You can end the spell early as a Bonus Action.\n\nOnce you use this feature, you can't do so again until you finish a Long Rest."
  fields:
  - body: "[Packet 6](https://www.dndbeyond.com/sources/ua/ph-playtest-6)"

"Light Domain: Corona of Light":
  title: "Light Domain Level 17: Corona of Light"
  desc: "As a Magic action, you cause yourself to emit an aura of sunlight that lasts for 1 minute or until you dismiss it (no action required). You emit Bright Light in a 60-foot radius and Dim Light for an additional 30 feet. Your enemies in the Bright Light have Disadvantage on saving throws against your Radiance of the Dawn and any spell that deals Fire or Radiant damage."
  fields:
  - body: "[Packet 6](https://www.dndbeyond.com/sources/ua/ph-playtest-6)"


